  "text": "The Kafka consumer fetch flow follows this chain: (1) **Request building**: `AbstractFetch.prepareFetchRequests()` determines fetchable partitions per node using `FetchSessionHandler`, then `AbstractFetch.createFetchRequest()` builds a `FetchRequest.Builder` via `FetchRequest.Builder.forConsumer()`. (2) **Network poll/send**: In the new consumer, `FetchRequestManager.poll()` \u2192 `pollInternal()` wraps requests as `UnsentRequest` objects dispatched via `NetworkClientDelegate`. In the legacy consumer, `Fetcher.sendFetches()` \u2192 `sendFetchesInternal()` sends via `ConsumerNetworkClient`. (3) **Response parsing**: `AbstractFetch.handleFetchSuccess()` casts the `ClientResponse` to `FetchResponse`, iterates per-partition `PartitionData`, and wraps each into a `CompletedFetch` object placed into `FetchBuffer`. (4) **ConsumerRecords population**: `FetchCollector.collectFetch()` drains `FetchBuffer`, calls `CompletedFetch.fetchRecords()` to deserialize records into `ConsumerRecord` lists, aggregates them into a `Fetch<K,V>` object whose records map is used to construct `ConsumerRecords`.",
